result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Frederick John Ziemer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Frederick John Ziemer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Frederick John Ziemer was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Edward Minser, DF ATTY: Joseph Robert Caton, DF: Frederick John Ziemer appeared.  Court called at 2:25 p.m.  Set for STC.   Includes case 14CF477 & 15CM23.  There is an agreement.  State files a 12 month DJOC on Ct. 1 in 14CF477.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to Ct 1 & Ct. 3 in 14CF477.  Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and stays the adjudication of guilt upon the pending full performance of the probation for Ct. 3 in 14CF477 and DJOC for Ct. 1 in 14CF477.  Court finds the DE adjudicated guilty of Ct. 3 in 14CF477.  On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 14CF477 & 15CM23. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

Ct. 1 in 14CF477
- Court reviews the 12 month DJOC with the DE and accepts the agreement and signs the order

Ct. 3 in 14CF477
- W/S 1 year probation with conditions
- AODA and follow through with any recommended treatment or therapy at the discretion of the probation agent
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

- DE to report to probation today 02/11/16
- 20 days to appeal
